tronion de pomme = 1 à 5 mois; 60g
chewing-gum = 5 ans; 5 g
mégots = 1-5 ans (1 mégot pollue jusqu'à 500 litres d'eau); 2g
boîte de polystyrène = 50 ans, 20g
briquet en plastique = 100 ans; 20g
masque chirurgical = 400 à 450 ans; 4g
canette de soda = 100 ans; 20g
sac plastique = 450 ans; 5g
carte sim = 1000ans; 2g
verre = 500 ans; 900g
pile au mercure = 200 ans
ampoule = + de 1000 ans; 15g
boite de conserve = 50 ans; 70g
brique de lait = 5 mois; 18g


FAITS :
  - tronion de pomme = 1 à 5 mois; 60g; COMP
  - chewing-gum = 5 ans; 5 g ; MEN
  - mégots = 1-5 ans; 2g ; MEN
  - boîte de polystyrène = 50 ans, 20g ; JAUNE
  - briquet en plastique = 100 ans; 20g ; MEN (depending on countries)
  - masque chirurgical = 400 à 450 ans; 4g ; MEN
  - canette de soda = 100 ans; 20g ; JAUNE
  - sac plastique = 450 ans; 5g ; JAUNE
  - verre = 500 ans; 900g ; MEN
  - pile au mercure = 200 ans ; OTHER
  - ampoule halogène / à filament = + de 1000 ans; 15g ; MEN
  - boite de conserve = 50 ans; 70g ; JAUNE
  - brique de lait = 5 mois; 18g ; JAUNE
  - flacon de parfum = 125g; VERT

À FAIRE :
  - papier = 2 semaines à 1 an; 5g ; VERT
  - carte sim = 1000ans; 2g ; JAUNE
  - journaux = 6 à 12 mois ; 35g ; BLEU
  - boite pizza = MEN
  - gel douche / shampoing = 300g ; JAUNE
  - déodorant à bille = 0.16 g; JAUNE
  - flacon vernis à ongles = 31g; VERT
  - déodorant / laque (pschiiit) = 150 ; JAUNE
  - déodorant (stick) = 78g ; MEN
  - rouge à lèvre / mascara / fard à paupière = MEN
  - boite en carton = 160g ; JAUNE
  - bouteille de vin = 500 g ; VERT
  - bocal = 70-140 g ; VERT
  - enveloppes = BLEU
  - livres = BLEU
  - Cahiers = Bleu
  - Dictionnaire LAROUSSE = Bleu
  - Film d'emballage = MEN
  - tube de dentifrice = MEN
  - tube de mayo = MEN
  - pelure banane = 1 à 6 mois ; 100g ; COMP 
  - ticket de caisse = BLEU
  - Gants plastic = MEN
  - pile AAA = OTHER
  - LEDS = OTHER
  - Already consumed meat/fish = MEN
  - Bay leaf(laurier) = OTHER
  - Stale bread = COMPOST
  
  
I BET YOU DIDN'T KNOW DAT:
  - On cigarette butts :
    -> 137M thrown on the floor per day on Earth :( (+30M in France)
    -> Although not a popular practice, butts can be recycled in comport & into
      fabrication related to plastic materials
    -> A butt can polute up to 500 liters of water :(
  - On polystyrene :
    -> Huge materials made of polysterene are to be thrown directly at a landfill
  - On make-up :
    -> Certain make-ups can be recycled and others not (when their composition contains plastic)
    -> To get more informed about where to throw them out visit incibeauty.com/ingredients
  - On carton boxes :
    -> Gotta fold em, not poupée russing them
  - On lass :
    -> Glass Jars and bottles are to be thrown in the garbage for glass
    -> BUT drinking glasses / tableware have a different chemical composition => to be thrown in household trash
    -> Separate the lids / caps (thrown in JAUNE)
  - On pizza boxes :
    -> When the box is soaked with oil => throw in MEN
  - On plastic :
    - When the plastic is thin & smooth (film) => thrown in MEN
  - On paper :
    -> A method of recycling developped by Sameer Madanshetty (ingeneer from Kansas State University)
       would make paper infinetely reusable !
  - On bulbs:
    -> LED and fluorescents bulbs are reusable and must be thrown in a store's destined bin
    -> in France find the list of these spaces in malampe.org by Recyclum
  - On batteries :
    -> They are too toxic for the environment and shouldn't be thrown in MEN ! Must be collected in dedicaded bins
    -> Find where you can thrown them on Corepile.net !
  - On lighters :
    -> Be careful ! Throw em in MEN only if they are empty 
    -> Otherwise you should get it collected to be professionnally thrown out (DON'T TRY REMOVING THE REMAIN OF LIQUID YOURSELF)
  - On consumed meat :
    -> It's prohibited to throw em in COMP because their biodegradation release a very bad odor 
  - On bay leaf :
    -> Every parts of a bay leaf is very toxic (try not to touch it) => immediately get it to the landfill
  - On stale bread :
    -> If it's only you can reuse it into breadcrumbs !
    -> If you insist on throwing it out, spread it in the COMP
    -> If it's rotten => soak it in water before throwing it
